# Streamlit Page Conventions

## Required Boilerplate (top of every page)

```python
from configs.i18n import lang_selector, t
from configs.settings import settings

st.set_page_config(page_title=t("mypage.page_title"), page_icon="...", layout="wide")
st.title(t("mypage.title"))

IS_DEMO = settings.demo_mode
if IS_DEMO:
    st.warning(t("common.demo_banner"), icon="🔒")
```

## Language Selector

Place `lang_selector()` as the **first item** in every sidebar:

```python
with st.sidebar:
    lang_selector()           # must be first
    st.header(t("..."))
    ...
```

## i18n — No Hardcoded UI Strings

```python
# ✅ GOOD
st.button(t("curves.button_load"))
st.error(t("curves.error_api", error=e))

# ❌ BAD — never hardcode English (or any language) in page files
st.button("Load curve")
```

Add missing keys to `configs/i18n.py` in all 3 languages before using them.

## Caching Pattern

```python
@st.cache_resource(show_spinner=t("mypage.spinner_session"))
def get_service(date: date) -> MyService:
    return MyService(market_date=date)

@st.cache_data(show_spinner=t("mypage.spinner_download"))
def fetch_data(_svc: MyService, ...) -> pd.DataFrame:
    return _svc.download(...)
```

- `@st.cache_resource` — for service/session objects (expensive to create)
- `@st.cache_data` — for API call results (keyed on serialisable args)
- Prefix unhashable args with `_` to exclude from cache key

## Demo Mode

- Show `common.demo_banner` warning at the top
- In sidebar, show `common.demo_cta_sidebar` after a `st.divider()`
- At page bottom after results, show `common.demo_cta_bottom` with `st.info(..., icon="ℹ️")`
- Disable date/side inputs when `IS_DEMO` is True
- Filter selectors to demo-available options only
